## 1. Purpose
This register is the single, authoritative index of every controlled ISMS document at [COMPANY]: its ID, current approved version, owner, approver, effective date, and review status. It is the mechanism by which `document-control.md.template` (POL-GOV-10) is operated — it makes overdue reviews visible, proves each document has a named owner and a recorded approval, and gives assessors one place to verify the document set is current.

## 2. Scope
All controlled documents within the ISMS scope (`isms-scope-statement.md.template`): policies, procedures, standards, plans, and registers — including this one. Uncontrolled working notes and drafts that have never been approved are out of scope until they enter the document lifecycle.

## 3. How to Use This Register
1. Add a row when a new controlled document enters DRAFT; update it at every approval, review, and supersession.
2. **Version** is the currently effective approved version (or the draft version if none is yet approved) per POL-GOV-10 §6.
3. **Next Review** must be at most 12 months after Last Reviewed; the [Security Officer] flags overdue rows and tracks them as corrective actions in `corrective-action-poam.md.template`.
4. **Ack Required** marks documents workforce members must acknowledge (e.g., Acceptable Use); acknowledgement evidence lives with [HR / LMS records].
5. Retired documents are marked `Superseded`/`Retired`, never deleted — retention follows POL-GOV-10 §8 (6-year HIPAA minimum).

**Status values:** `Draft` · `Approved` · `In Review` · `Superseded` · `Retired`.

