## 5. Roles & Responsibilities
| Role | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| [Security Officer / CISO] | Owns and maintains the register; flags overdue reviews; reports document-set currency at management review. |
| Document Owners | Keep their rows current; initiate reviews before Next Review. |
| Approvers | Sign off on new versions; approval is recorded here and in the document's Version History. |

See `roles-and-responsibilities.md.template` for full role definitions.

## 6. Exceptions
Deviations from register maintenance (e.g., a document tracked outside this register) require documented risk acceptance per `exceptions-and-waivers.md.template`, approved by the [Security Officer].

## 7. Compliance, Monitoring & Enforcement
The register is reviewed at internal audit (`internal-audit-program.md.template`) and management review (`management-review.md.template`) as the primary evidence that document control operates. Overdue reviews and unowned documents are tracked as corrective actions per `corrective-action-poam.md.template`.

